item.title: I scare my self. (sleep typing I is posable)
item.dc:creator: Dr_Strangelove
item.description:
Sorry darkone, but there is nothing special about you.

You are just going through the stage in your life that involves trying to develop a true identity. You are trying to differentiate yourself by thinking you are crazy. In truth, it’s perfectly normal, a lot of people think that way when they are trying to figure out who they are. But really, if you aren’t honest with yourself it could lead to problems later on. You could sink into confusion and be unable to make decisions and choices about things like vocation, sexual orientation, and just your general role in life.

You should grow out of it in a couple of years.

item.title: I scare my self. (sleep typing I is posable)
item.dc:creator: mattemuse
item.description:
hercule poirots nutsack:

tupac is alive

Sug had Tupac and BIG assasinated. Unless Pac = Jesus (which I admit is a possibility) he’s still dead.

darkone:

i want to be part wolf

Too bad, you aren’t. Even .0001%. Confused adolescent nerds are the farthest possible thing from wolves, you have less in common with a wolf than anything else I can imagine, animal vegetable or mineral. The Hindenburg was more wolflike than you are. This kind of thing is why children shouldn’t be allowed to read the internet (and especially forums) until they are 18. If you hadn’t gotten the retarded - sorry, developmentally impaired - idea from some furry forum somewhere, you’d be working out your preteen angst in a more constructive manner rather than feeding it with a self-perpetuating cycle of fan-fiction concocted by similarly confused nerds.
The tragedy is that this environment only prolongs the INEVITABLE moment whether it’s 6 months from now or 6 years, that you come to the realization that it was all nonsense.

Funny story, I have no recollection of writing the above paragraph.
